abstract = {This chapter discusses the importance of the analysis of new psychoactive substances (NPS) in wastewater as a strategy to assess the consumption of these substances by the population and to control the impact of the global drug market. In this sense, the analytical strategies that allow carrying these analyses are presented, from sample collection, sample preparation for analysis and the main instrumental techniques used. The different approaches for instrumental data treatment to obtain information about the presence of new psychoactive substances and their translation to the field of drug consumption by the population are an important aspect to consider. A summary of the different studies carried out at national and international levels about the identification of new psychoactive substances in wastewater is presented. Finally, the main challenges of this type of analysis are discussed focussed on the handling and preparation of wastewater samples, developments and expectations in analytical instrumentation, selection of adequate biomarkers, data processing and the importance of NPS and metabolite references.}
}
